						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra Narasiṁha, 1506 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record seems to be dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14., Krōdhana,</hi> the other details being lost. The Śaka year corresponding to Krōdhana would be 1428 (current) <hi rend="bold">1506 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It appears to record some gift, probably of land, in the village Pāṇem in Peḍakaṇṭisīma to the god Svyaṁbhu-Mallikārjuna on the auspicious occasion of Kanyā Bṛihaspati. as in No. 43 above.</p>						

						</summary>
